quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  51,7,"And by oath of the decorated heaven."
  51,8,"You are indeed in different opinions regarding this Qur’an."
  51,9,"Only those who are destined to revert, are reverted from it."
  51,10,"Slain be those who mould from their imaginations."
  51,11,"Those who have forgotten in a state of intoxication."
  51,12,"They ask, “When will be the Day of Judgement?”"
  51,13,"It will be on the day when they will be roasted in the fire."
  51,14,"And it will be said to them, “Taste your own roasting; this is what you were impatient for.”"
  51,15,"Indeed the pious are among Gardens and water springs."
  51,16,"Accepting the rewards given by their Lord; they were indeed virtuous before this."
  51,17,"They used to sleep only a little during the night."
  51,18,"And used to seek forgiveness before dawn."
  51,19,"And the beggar and the destitute had a share in their wealth."
  51,20,"And in the earth are signs for those who are certain."
  51,21,"And in your own selves; so can you not perceive?"
  51,22,"And in the heaven lies your sustenance, and the promise you are given."
  51,23,"So by oath of the Lord of the heavens and the earth, this Qur’an is the Truth, in the same language that you speak."
  51,24,"Did the news of Ibrahim’s honourable guests reach you (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him)?"
  51,25,"When they came to him and said, “Peace”; he answered, “Peace”; and thought, “These people are not familiar.”"
  51,26,"Then he went to his home – so he brought a healthy calf."
  51,27,"He then presented it before them and said, “Do you not eat?”"
  51,28,"He therefore inwardly sensed fear of them; they said, “Do not fear!”; and they gave him the glad tidings of a knowledgeable son."
  51,29,"So his wife came screaming, and striking her forehead cried, “What! For a barren old woman?”"
  51,30,"They said, “This is how your Lord has decreed; indeed He only is the Wise, the All Knowing.”"
